MOVING SUPPORT CENTER

3
00:00:37,787 --> 00:00:39,539
Oh, it's snowing.

4
00:00:49,966 --> 00:00:51,342
-Hey.
-Gosh.

5
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:54,179
You're already up and working
so early in the morning.

6
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:55,096
Good morning.

7
00:00:56,222 --> 00:00:58,725
Isn't this for your daughter in Seoul?

8
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:00,477
You mean my Bo-ra?

9
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:04,647
-Take care.
-Yeah. Be careful on the road.

10
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:27,587
I feel you with the breeze.

11
00:01:28,713 --> 00:01:29,839
Goddess of the Wind.

12
00:01:30,548 --> 00:01:33,218
Okay. Good work, Ms. Na. Let's go eat.

13
00:01:33,301 --> 00:01:34,511
Good work, everyone.

14
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:36,805
-Good work. Let's go eat.
-Great work.

15
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:41,476
Yeah, Dad.

16
00:01:41,559 --> 00:01:43,520
Who's Joseph?

17
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:45,688
Huh? Who?

18
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:48,108
Are you dating some foreigner?

19
00:01:48,608 --> 00:01:50,193
What are you talking about?

20
00:01:50,276 --> 00:01:54,447
"A forbidden love of everyone's dreams"?

21
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:56,991
Are you still watching porn?

22
00:01:57,075 --> 00:02:00,161
What are you talking about?
When did I ever watch porn?

23
00:02:00,245 --> 00:02:04,624
Fine, then. There's no need
to yell at your father.

24
00:02:04,707 --> 00:02:08,128
I got all excited for nothing.
I thought you were seeing someone.

25
00:02:08,211 --> 00:02:11,172
Hey. Are you coming down here
when we move or not?

26
00:02:11,256 --> 00:02:14,342
-Oh, uh--
-It's okay if you're too busy to come.

27
00:02:14,425 --> 00:02:17,887
It's fine. We can just sprain our backs
carrying all this heavy stuff.

28
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:20,390
-No, I--
-What can I do? Our kids are too busy.

29
00:02:20,473 --> 00:02:21,724
Do whatever you want!

30
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:23,226
Okay.

31
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:31,609
THE LOVE AFFAIR

32
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:37,782
A FORBIDDEN LOVE OF EVERYONE'S DREAMS

33
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:53,631
Hey, Kim Yeon-doo, are you crazy?

34
00:02:55,466 --> 00:02:56,301
Huh?

35
00:02:56,885 --> 00:02:59,345
1999, CHEONGJU

36
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,355
Why are you suddenly not going to America?

37
00:03:10,356 --> 00:03:12,150
Don't you need the heart surgery?

38
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:15,737
What use is surgery
when I don't have a heart?

39
00:03:17,530 --> 00:03:19,449
What on Earth are you saying?

40
00:03:19,532 --> 00:03:23,036
My heart was stolen.

41
00:03:25,496 --> 00:03:26,748
Welcome.

42
00:03:32,086 --> 00:03:34,839
Oh, my mother is not here right now.

43
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:37,717
Excuse me!

44
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:40,929
I can measure sizes too.

45
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:43,097
Just hold on.

46
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:47,602
Huh?

47
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:53,733
Ouch.

48
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,504
BAEK HYUN-JIN

49
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:17,006
Has your heart ever fluttered

50
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:19,300
in a life-threatening way?

51
00:04:21,469 --> 00:04:23,346
Isn't that due to your heart condition?

52
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:26,474
No. It was definitely different.

53
00:04:26,557 --> 00:04:28,309
Have you ever seen me act like this?

54
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:30,853
Lee Jae-ung,
the fifth-grade class president.

55
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:32,855
Choi Yeong-su, middle school track team.

56
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:34,774
The assistant art teacher
in middle school.

57
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:36,943
Let's see, who else? Oh, yeah!

58
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:43,241
Hey, didn't you say that Jung-jae
would be your last love?

59
00:04:43,324 --> 00:04:44,951
So did I do all that for nothing?

60
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:49,539
This time, it's really, truly real.

61
00:04:50,498 --> 00:04:52,458
I can't fall asleep at night
since that day.

62
00:04:53,042 --> 00:04:54,919
I'm scared I won't see him again,

63
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:57,130
and just listening to music makes me cry.

64
00:04:57,922 --> 00:04:59,465
It's serious for me.

65
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:03,886
You still can't do this!
Hurry, start packing!

66
00:05:04,804 --> 00:05:07,640
Hey, you think I'm being like this
for no reason?

67
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:12,312
He got the uniform for Wooam High,
the same school as ours.

68
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:14,355
So how am I supposed to just leave?

69
00:05:23,531 --> 00:05:26,451
WOULD YOU LIKE TO CREATE AN EMAIL ACCOUNT?

70
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:29,871
ID BORA1999

71
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:30,997
ID YEONDOO1999

72
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:34,250
The password is "friends forever."

73
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:36,419
What am I supposed to do with this?

74
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:41,716
From now on, you'll know everything
that he does.

75
00:05:41,799 --> 00:05:43,551
As if you're going to school with him.

76
00:05:43,634 --> 00:05:44,469
Bo-ra…

77
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:50,350
So go get your surgery
and come back healthy, okay?

78
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:51,267
Okay!

79
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,940
HYUN-JIN OBSERVATION NOTES

80
00:05:58,024 --> 00:06:01,527
Dear Bo-ra, I'm writing this
as soon as I got to my aunt's.

81
00:06:01,611 --> 00:06:03,696
It's a whole new world here.

82
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:06,616
America is huge,
and the buildings are super tall too.

83
00:06:07,116 --> 00:06:07,950
BORA VIDEO

84
00:06:08,034 --> 00:06:10,787
And there are people who look
like movie stars everywhere, seriously.

85
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:14,916
It sucks to be hospitalized,
missing out on such great things.

86
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:17,543
I wish you were here with me
to just have fun.

87
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:21,506
So, today's finally
your first day of school.

88
00:06:21,589 --> 00:06:22,799
Wake your sister up!

89
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:26,427
You didn't oversleep again, did you?

90
00:06:27,261 --> 00:06:29,430
Na Bo-ra's awake, Mom.

91
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:32,517
Wow, really?
Maybe pigs will start flying soon.

92
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,310
Go tell her to eat breakfast.

93
00:06:36,104 --> 00:06:37,939
Huh? Did she already leave?

94
00:06:38,022 --> 00:06:38,856
BORA VIDEO

95
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,608
Today's the big day!
You're going to see that boy.

96
00:06:40,691 --> 00:06:42,985
-Wait, what…
-Just thinking about it excites me!

97
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:45,154
Huh? Did she leave already?

98
00:06:45,238 --> 00:06:48,574
That day, I saw him walking
toward the apartment complex.

99
00:06:48,658 --> 00:06:50,410
Instead of our neighborhood bus stop,

100
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:53,413
run to Lucky Apartments
and catch the bus there.

101
00:06:54,122 --> 00:06:56,040
Then you might meet him sooner.

102
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:59,669
Mister, wait for me! Mister!

103
00:07:03,673 --> 00:07:04,799
Thank you, sir.

104
00:07:04,882 --> 00:07:06,134
I'm sorry. Excuse me.

105
00:07:07,301 --> 00:07:09,429
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

106
00:07:14,016 --> 00:07:14,851
I'm sorry!

107
00:07:21,315 --> 00:07:23,609
Mister, slow down!

108
00:07:24,193 --> 00:07:25,027
Sit here.

109
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:27,029
Don't trip again.

110
00:07:27,905 --> 00:07:29,031
Thank you.

111
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:34,328
Remember, his name is Baek Hyun-jin.

112
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:35,413
BAEK HYUN-JIN

113
00:07:37,331 --> 00:07:39,083
Let's go to the school shop later.

114
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:40,001
Sure.

115
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:42,545
-You're buying this time.
-Why?

116
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:44,380
There you are. Baek Hyun-jin.

117
00:07:45,339 --> 00:07:46,382
WELCOME, 1999 SCHOOL YEAR

118
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:48,301
Hello, freshmen.

119
00:07:48,384 --> 00:07:50,470
Boys over here, girls over there.

120
00:07:52,763 --> 00:07:54,557
You punk, what the heck is this outfit?

121
00:07:57,935 --> 00:07:59,437
-Where are you going?
-Sorry?

122
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:02,356
Girls go this way, and boys go that way.
Come on, go inside!

123
00:08:03,691 --> 00:08:05,443
Huh? Darn It?

124
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:10,281
Ugh, darn it.

125
00:08:10,907 --> 00:08:13,284
I was excited to come to a co-ed school,

126
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:15,328
but it's the same as an all-girls school.

127
00:08:15,411 --> 00:08:18,498
That doesn't mean all hope is lost.

128
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:21,375
-Madam?
-Madam?

129
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:29,091
Once the bell rings,
all the famished boys and girls

130
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:31,260
will mix and mingle in one place.

131
00:08:41,145 --> 00:08:42,438
Gosh! Slow down.

132
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:43,731
Line up! Slowly!

133
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:53,324
Bo-ra.

134
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:55,993
I need you to do something now.

135
00:08:56,911 --> 00:08:58,120
I'm counting on you.

136
00:09:09,465 --> 00:09:11,759
EVERYTHING YEON-DOO WANTS TO KNOW
ABOUT "THAT BOY"

137
00:09:11,842 --> 00:09:13,636
He's 181 centimeters tall.

138
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:16,847
He likes orange-flavored Demisoda.

139
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:18,057
And his shoe size?

140
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:19,267
280.

141
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:21,018
He likes basketball.

142
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:24,480
If he's good at basketball,
he must be super popular.

143
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:28,568
Kind of. But not enough
for you to be worried.

144
00:09:28,651 --> 00:09:30,444
-How are his friends?
-Basketball later?

145
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:32,280
What if he has a girlfriend?

146
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:36,867
I don't think so.
But he's always with his best friend.

147
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:38,536
Poong Woon-ho, a guy in his class.

148
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:40,788
He lives in building 304
at Lucky Apartments.

149
00:09:40,871 --> 00:09:42,373
They commute to school together.

150
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:45,501
Do you think there's a way
to get closer to him?

151
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:48,004
-So, there's a sense of community.
-Clubs?

152
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:53,843
What are the principles
a democratic citizen must uphold?

153
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:57,888
First, respect discussions and debates.

154
00:09:57,972 --> 00:10:00,516
-Woon-ho!
-Hey, this way…

155
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,518
-Am I right or not?
-You're right.

156
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:04,604
Two, give way to…

157
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:08,441
What?

158
00:10:10,234 --> 00:10:11,402
Sorry?

159
00:10:12,987 --> 00:10:13,904
Oh…

160
00:10:17,658 --> 00:10:18,659
Ow!

161
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:21,621
Hey, my stomach hurts.

162
00:10:22,788 --> 00:10:25,416
Sir, my stomach hurts so much.

163
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,377
I think I need to go to the nurse.

164
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:30,171
-Does it hurt?
-No, it doesn't.

165
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:32,340
Stop it.

166
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,175
Huh? Oh.

167
00:10:35,885 --> 00:10:38,137
-Next.
-Why aren't you going?

168
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:40,598
I'm guessing you don't need to see me?

169
00:10:40,681 --> 00:10:42,391
Huh? Oh, yes, sir.

170
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:48,522
Sir, I have really bad period cramps.

171
00:10:48,606 --> 00:10:50,524
Oh, you have cramps?

172
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:53,486
Here.

173
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:56,697
Your hands.

174
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:00,910
Take this and rest here for a bit.

175
00:11:00,993 --> 00:11:02,495
-Thank you, sir.
-Sure.

176
00:11:02,995 --> 00:11:05,081
-Hope you feel better.
-Yes, sir.

177
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:06,040
Next.

178
00:11:06,123 --> 00:11:07,792
Hyeon-beom tackled you too hard.

179
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:09,585
Let him be. It just means I'm good.

180
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:12,004
Hey, did you pick a club to join?

181
00:11:13,464 --> 00:11:14,840
I don't know. You?

182
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:18,469
-The broadcasting club.
-Then I'll join them too.

183
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:21,305
Do you even know what they do?

184
00:11:21,389 --> 00:11:24,016
I don't know. What do they do?

185
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:26,435
Hey, they even have auditions.

186
00:11:27,228 --> 00:11:28,229
Wait.

187
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:35,736
What is it?

188
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:40,658
-Nothing.
-What?

189
00:11:41,742 --> 00:11:47,289
-What do they look for in the audition?
-Passionate voices? Something like that.

190
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:48,916
An enthusiastic voice?

191
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:50,876
How do you show people that?

192
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:53,713
Come on, hurry.

193
00:11:54,422 --> 00:11:55,923
Thank you.

194
00:11:56,632 --> 00:11:59,093
All right, number three, Na Bo-ra.

195
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:24,994
-I think she'll get in.
-Is she Na Bo-ra?

196
00:12:25,077 --> 00:12:26,203
Thank you.

197
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:29,123
Next, number four, Baek Hyun-jin.

198
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:38,382
I'm sorry, sir.

199
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:39,967
-What?
-What's he saying?

200
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:43,304
To make room for talented kids like her,

201
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:47,516
I'll be withdrawing from this audition.

202
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:52,062
You can all see
the yearly plan up front, right?

203
00:12:52,146 --> 00:12:53,355
-I got in.
-Yes, sir.

204
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:54,732
For the details--

205
00:12:54,815 --> 00:12:56,609
But Baek Hyun-jin isn't here.

206
00:12:56,692 --> 00:12:58,944
You guys are the future
of our broadcasting club.

207
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:01,781
Let's do our best for the next year.

208
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:02,698
Yes, sir!

209
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:03,908
-I'll do my best!
-Okay.

210
00:13:03,991 --> 00:13:05,367
Don't worry, though.

211
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:06,952
You'll work in pairs.

212
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:08,245
I have a great plan.

213
00:13:08,329 --> 00:13:10,122
-Be nice to your partner.
-Yes, sir.

214
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:13,584
Hey, Woon-ho!

215
00:13:15,669 --> 00:13:18,631
We're partners. I look forward
to working with you.

216
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:21,050
Okay.

217
00:13:22,176 --> 00:13:24,303
Hey, wait…

218
00:13:27,264 --> 00:13:28,098
"Okay"?

219
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:36,273
Huh? A pager?

220
00:13:56,335 --> 00:13:59,463
Zero one two…

221
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:05,302
Six…

222
00:14:09,014 --> 00:14:10,766
Zero…

223
00:14:11,851 --> 00:14:13,644
Let's go to the school shop after this.

224
00:14:13,727 --> 00:14:15,396
Hold on. I'm checking this.

225
00:14:16,856 --> 00:14:17,857
Okay, hurry up.

226
00:14:18,774 --> 00:14:19,900
Dang it.

227
00:14:20,651 --> 00:14:21,485
PHONE BOOK

228
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:24,613
BAEK GWANG-DEOK, BAEK GI-YONG, BAEK…

229
00:14:32,788 --> 00:14:33,706
Hello?

230
00:14:34,206 --> 00:14:36,208
May I speak with Baek Hyun-jin?

231
00:14:36,292 --> 00:14:37,960
Who? I don't know him.

232
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:38,878
Oh, uh--

233
00:14:44,592 --> 00:14:46,719
May I speak with Baek Hyun-jin?

234
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:48,220
-Wrong number.
-Yes, sir.

235
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:18,918
Please.

236
00:15:23,213 --> 00:15:24,048
Hello.

237
00:15:25,215 --> 00:15:27,301
May I speak with Baek Hyun-jin?

238
00:15:33,641 --> 00:15:34,725
Who is this?

239
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:42,274
This is the research institute, Yes or No.

240
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:45,694
What is your favorite pop song?

241
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:48,572
Please state your response after the beep.

242
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:50,824
Beep.

243
00:15:54,703 --> 00:15:56,747
"Time Like a Lie" by Toy.

244
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:02,461
Thank you for responding to our survey.

245
00:16:02,544 --> 00:16:05,047
We will be sending you a small gift.

246
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:08,926
Once you hear the beep,
please state your pager number.

247
00:16:11,887 --> 00:16:12,972
Beep.

248
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:18,060
Na Bo-ra?

249
00:16:22,856 --> 00:16:24,400
Crap.

250
00:16:37,955 --> 00:16:40,082
That was you yesterday, right?

251
00:16:42,292 --> 00:16:43,460
Of course not.

252
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:49,550
I mean…

253
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:51,135
What do you mean?

254
00:16:55,139 --> 00:16:56,932
Do you want Hyun-jin's pager number?

255
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:58,267
Huh? Baek Hyun-jin's?

256
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:03,480
Why on earth would I want
to know his pager number?

257
00:17:03,564 --> 00:17:04,398
So it was you.

258
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:06,608
Yes or No.

259
00:17:10,738 --> 00:17:12,906
What's the deal with you? Hey, you!

260
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:18,412
Why'd you pretend to be Hyun-jin
when you're not and answer his calls?

261
00:17:19,663 --> 00:17:21,331
I never said I was Hyun-jin.

262
00:17:22,332 --> 00:17:23,250
Whatever!

263
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:29,965
So, are you going to tell me?

264
